The call for papers for YSTS 3.0 is now open!
The 3th edition will be happening on June, 22nd 2009 in Sao Paulo, Brazil.

INTRODUCTION 

YSTS is a very unique event dedicated to the top-notch information Security
Society in Brazil, bringing legendary speakers from Brazil and abroad and,
mainly having the highest quality presentations, covering diverse topics in
information security, from technical to managements topics. 
The goal is make the attendees get the "real big picture" of the
information
security world, joinnig professionals from the same and different segments
of
the market to promote better all security areas knowledge. 


CONFERENCE TOPICS

The focus for YSTS 3.0 will include the following:
   * Operating Systems
   * Create and Manager of Information Security 
   * Mobile Devices/Embedded Systems
   * Information Security Audit and Control 
   * Web 2.0 or above
   * Information Security Policies 
   * Networking/Telecommunication/Radio Frequencies
   * Incident Response 
   * Information Warfare 
   * Malware
   * BotNets
   * Secure Programming
   * Virtualization 
   * 0day soccer tricks
   * Criptography/Obfuscation
   * Infrastructure Systems
   * Caipirinha Hacks 
   * or any topics that will catch the attention of the CFP committee
and/or the world

PRIVILEGES

Speakers' Privileges:

   * USD 1,000.00 to help covering travel expenses
   * Breakfast, lunch and dinner during conference
   * After-conference party
   * Auditing products in traditional brazilian barbecue restaurants


CPF SUBMISSION

NOTICE: We accept submissions in English, Portuguese and Spanish. 

CFP submission must include the following information: 

   * Name, title, address, email and phone/contact number 
   * Short biography and qualification
   * Speaking experience
   * Sumary or abstract for your presentation 
   * Techincal requeriments (others than LCD Projector) 
   * Other plublications or conferences where this material has been or 
     will be published/submitted. 

IMPORTANT DATES

Final CFP Submission - May 10th, 2009 
Notification of Acceptance - May 20th, 2009
Final Submission for accepted presentation material - June 15th, 2009

Please send your submiission to cfp/at/ysts.org 


